Downfall

by: Beckham Kunkler

This game was made for my level 2 project at The League of Amazing Programmers.
Click here to download and play!

1. Why I Made This Game

I was surfing the internet looking at games, and I found this game where you could only jump, and you would role down a path with spikes. I thought it would be cool to have it rolling down platforms, until my dad said I should make it so you are trying the dodge enemies, and you would jump in mid-air. I thought it would be really fun to make this game, because unlike other games, it changes over time, so the longer you stay alive, the harder it gets.

2. What I Learned

I needed to fix some bugs, and I really needed an off button on the music, because it gets very annoying. I also needed to change the spawning space of the lava and coins, because you couldn't see the coins sometimes.

3. Architecture of My Game

My game panel class uses the object manager's score, so they both can access it. my object manager uses the coin's and lava's methods, and changes their x and y values. my downfall class starts the game panel, and my object manager and game panel use my ball class.

4. Technical Implementation

I am very proud of my ball changing color depending on the score. It was hard because it took a while to place when the change randy, so it can change the color of the rainbow ball. It was also challenging to implement the win state, so when you die and have a score of 20 or more, it displays the win state. I fixed it, so I added an if statement for when you die, it checks your score, and when you restart, it also checks if the states is 5 or 3.

5. Most Challenging Part

The most difficult part, was getting the movement right for the ball, so it moves side to side at the right speed, and jumps at the right speed, and counteracts the force of gravity. I fixed moving side to side be making it so it always wants to not move side to side, so you wont drift on forever. But I just did a lot of trial and error to find the right amount to jump at the right height.

6. Future Fixes and Updates

Adding a pause menu would make it a lot easier to take photos. I also would really want to add more colors for the ball, and difficulty levels, for more and less lavas and coins.
